Package: CatchThemAll.PRM
Title: Calculate Pollutant Risk Metric (PRM) values from pollutant concentrations...Catch them all
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alexander", "Bezzina", ,"alex.h.bezzina@gmail.com", 
    role = c("aut", "cre", "cph")),
    person("Jennifer", "Strauss", ,"jennifer.strauss@des.qld.gov.au",
    role = "aut"),
    person("Catherine", "Neelamraju", ,"c.neelamraju@uq.edu.au",
    role = "aut"),
    person("Hayley", "Kaminski", ,"hayley.kaminski@des.qld.gov.au",
    role = "aut"))
Description: This packages contains functions which can be used to calculate
    Pollutant Risk Metric values for concentrations of multiple pollutants with known
    species sensative distributions (SSDs). Pollutants provided by this package have 
    all be validated however if the user has their own pollutants with SSD values they
    can append them to the pollutant_info table to include them in estimates.
